The private schools in Scotland are known for their students’ outstanding achievements and it has continued into 2018 with new, elegant test results, which are still reinforced by individual and group achievements in sports, arts, music and other societies.
These schools have up to 30,000 students across Scotland, with The Scottish Council of Independent Schools (SCIS) in charge of them, and they compete to provide their students and their parents with the best possible service.
