68 percent of students who learned a foreign language received the A score.
The data, collected from 74 schools within the SCIS, showed that 72 percent of students received an A grade in Mandarin, while 72 percent of those who learned German, 69 percent of those who learned French, and 63 percent of those who learned Spanish also received an A grade.
