At the moment, languages, such as electives, are placed in the same place as scientific subjects (science, technology, engineering and mathematics) in the curricula of private schools and elsewhere.
A 2014 survey by the UK Commission for Employment and Skills found that, for the reasons that employers found it difficult to get a job, there was a 17 per cent shortage of people with language skills.
