Now that more and more jobs require proficiency in languages, this skill is essential in a nationalized world.
No matter what career path people choose, it will have a real head start in the future if they learn another language, but it is a skill that will last a lifetime.
Being able to have direct communication with people from other countries will automatically give a multi-talented person an advantage over the competitor.
According to a survey conducted by YouGov on over 4,000 British adults in 2013, 75 percent of them could not speak another language well enough to hold talks, and French was the only language spoken by two-digit percentages, or 15 percent.
