Multilingualism, especially in new-market countries, will give children a better chance of finding a meaningful job.
In Scotland, it is different between schools what language they teach.
A certain number of schools will focus on classic new languages, while others will teach languages that are considered to be most important to the UK when viewed until 2020, such as Mandarin or Japanese.
