Latest news of turmeric flowers: Concentrations decrease in Pinellas, Manatee and Sarasota
The latest news from the Florida Fish and Wildlife Commission shows a general decrease in the concentration of deciduous flowers in parts of the Tampa Bay area.
According to the FWC, more worn turf flowers are reported in certain areas of Pinellas, Manatee, Sarasota Charlotte and Collier counties - indicating a decrease in density.
The stork flower covers about 200 kilometres of coastline from the northern part of Pinellas to the southern part of Lee County.
You can find unique flowers about 16 kilometers from Hillsborough County, but in fewer places compared to last week.
There have also been reports of turpentine blooms in Pasco County.
Moderate to moderate concentrations at or near Pinellas County were reported in the last week of low to moderate concentrations at the coasts of Hillsborough County, very low to moderate concentrations in Manatee County, very low to moderate concentrations in or near Sara County.
There have also been reports of respiratory irritation in Pinellas, Manatee, Sarasota, Lee and Collier counties.
